    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>re: Portland Farmer&#8217;s Market &#8212; it is seriously getting incredible, it&#8217;s so exciting!  I bought some hood strawberries Saturday, that looked a bit iffy and they were amazing, but we have already had strawberries (they&#8217;ve been growing them in greenhouses) for almost a month that have been pretty darn good.  We&#8217;re so, so lucky here.</></>Btw,  I made this salad last week, and it was delicious, simple, and a perfect quick weeknight meal.  I found some fabulous lemon basil at the store that I sprinkled on top instead of parsley, it really brightened it.</p>
